phrases: I hope you are having a good time.
There is going to be a fireworks festival in Higashi-cho today.
I get the whole day off today.
I am going to forget about the quintuplets and study all I want!
I should teach them this formula.
Even Yotsuba could learn from it.
This one would be good for Miku.
Wait, what the hell am I doing?!
What am I, a tryhard tutor?!
If you are here for money, we do not have...
Why did you close the door on me?
There is something I need to give you.
My father left your pay with me.
You are turning Yukichi-san wrinkly with your sweat!
Five thousand yen a day for each of us.
That is fifty thousand yen for two days.
We will be able to pay off the loans in no time.
Well, I will be leaving now.
Sure, I did go to your place twice.
But I did not do anything.
I thought we cleared that up!
I do not think it is true that you have done nothing.
Your presence is beginning to change something in the five of us.
A-Anyway, I will not take this back.
Raiha, is there anything you want?
I want to try going to the arcade!
You will come too, will not you, Itsuki-san?
Raiha has a hard time because of our family situation.
I am sure there are many more things she would like to do.
I want to grant all of her wishes.
I want to do that one with the two of you before we go.
On second thought, I am going to pass.
It is like a family photo.
What kind of face is that?
I will cherish this for the rest of my life.
No, I still have the evening.
All of you had better study tonight, too.
Why are you with him, Itsuki?!
Were you in the middle of a date?
Let us go see the fireworks together.
We are going to miss the start of the fireworks!
When are the fireworks starting again?
They are from 7 PM to 8 PM.
I am going to check out the stalls!
Well, at least they did their homework for once.
Is that how badly they want to see the fireworks?
What is with that unfestive look on your face?
You girls are hard enough to tell apart as it is.
Do not go changing your hairstyle.
And I am free to do my hair however I please!
When a girl changes her hairstyle,
Hey, do not you want to find out if girls truly wear nothing under their yukatas?
That was a long time ago.
Did I get your heart racing a bit?
What are you all doing here?
It was supposed to be just the five of us here for the fireworks.
I am just here with my sister.
Yotsuba-san caught all these for me.
Could not you have held back a little?
Seeing Raiha-chan, I could not help but want to get her a gift.
That is the last thing we need today!
Did you say thank you to Yotsuba?
I want to make you my sister!
If I married Uesugi-san, we would legally be sisters.
Do you realize what you are saying?
And you better not get any weird ideas about Yotsuba!
Nino rented out a shop's rooftop.
We have come out to a festival,
and we are not going to buy the thing?
We have not bought the thing.
Are you talking about the thing?
Was there a food stand selling the thing?
I cannot wait to have the thing!
Let us go buy it all!
I am starting to wonder if you are really quintuplets.
Raiha, stay close, or you will get lost.
That shop owner... I do not like him.
I will give ya some freebies, pretty lady.
Want to go play ring toss?
You all seem pretty excited, too.
Fireworks were a big part of memories we shared with our mom.
She loved the fireworks, so we all went together every year.
Every year, even after Mom went away.
No wonder she is so gung-ho.
The fireworks are about to begin.
We will never get anywhere standing here.
Take me to the shop you rented out.
Just so you know, you are not invited.
Are not the five of you going to watch the fireworks together?
On the roof of this building.
Come to think of it, I am the only one who knows where the shop is.
There is a theory that Tokugawa Ieyasu was the first to see fireworks in Japan.
Fireworks were invented in China, but they went through Europe
and arrived in Japan's Tanegashima along with firearms.
What did I do to deserve having to watch the fireworks with you?
I cannot get a hold of them on their phones, either.
I worked so hard to finish my homework, too.
Fireworks were a big part of memories we shared with our mom.
I do not want to be alone with you anyway.
Let us go back to the shop.
What is your relationship with Ichika-chan?
I am surprised you managed to find me.
Well, you were sticking out like a sore thumb.
I have to go after Ichika.
Miku, can you see Ichika from up there?
You are not actually going to chase after her like this, are you?
You are heavy, so I cannot chase after her.
Want me to buy you some takoyaki, Raiha-chan?
Oh, there is yakisoba over there.
Yotsuba-san, we have to stay here.
So, did you really see Ichika?
but she took off with some dude with a mustache.
Any idea who it might have been?
I think I have seen her getting out of some mustachioed man's car.
I hope there is nothing sketchy going on between them.
The fireworks are going to be over before you five get together.
You are being helpful, even though this has nothing to do with studying.
I would not expect that from you.
I am invested in this now.
Besides, I watched you all desperately do your homework for this.
We are surveying people who came to see the the fireworks today.
What is the relationship between the two of you?
What is your relationship with Ichika-chan?
Oh, I guess there was no need to ask.
The two of them are a couple.
W-We are not in a relationship.
But that is clearly what it looks like.
The two of us are friends.
Or should I just say schoolmates?
I guess that is not quite enough.
Could not you hide your disappointment a little?
Let us meet up with her.
Now we are just missing Ichika.
What is with that creepy question?
Besides, you do not need to ask me.
You already have the answer to that question.
Are not you going to watch with the others?
Anyway, do not tell anyone about what happened earlier.
I cannot watch the fireworks with the rest of you.
Next Time on The Quintessential Quintuplets
I shall be announcing the sum of the quintuplets' breast sizes.
What is wrong with this robot?
Eighty-eight times five makes 444 centimeters, right?
Okay, that is enough of that!
